OL,6,FThe headline-grabbing elements of the
OL,7,Fgovernment's new law to crack down on
OL,8,Fstreet harassment are that it will ban
OL,9,Fwolf-whistling or catcalling.
OL,11,FBut the kinds of behaviours referenced
OL,12,Fin the consultation ranged far beyond
OL,13,Fthis. They include suggestive language,
OL,14,Fgestures or propositioning; following a
OL,15,Fvictim or slowing to block their path;
OL,16,Fand staring or leering.
OL,18,FThe decision to come forward with this
OL,19,Flaw is, as the Home Secretary herself
OL,20,Fsaid, a "complex" one.
